2282e2f8-474f-4da9-a7f0-a667f59a81f5.text:
Title:How to check the connection to your home network and the internet | Official Roku Support
Error codes:

1. None mentioned in the text.

Solutions:

1. Check the quality of the connection from the Settings menu on the Roku device.
2. If the Roku device is not connected to the network, select Set up connection to connect to the network and the internet before continuing.
3. If a connection check shows a red x for Wireless or Wired connection, then return to the Network menu, select Set up connection, and try to connect the Roku device to the network. If uncertain about selecting the correct network, get help finding the wireless network name and password. If the problem continues, learn what to do if the Roku device cannot access the home network.
4. If a connection check shows a red x for Internet connection, then test the internet connection at home using a computer or a mobile device connected to the home network. If the computer or mobile device cannot access the internet, contact the ISP and inquire about an outage in the area. If the computer or mobile device can access the internet, double-check that the Roku device is connected to the correct wireless network. If the problem continues, restart the Roku device and the router.
5. To restart the router, unplug it and plug it back in or press the reset button on the device. For more help, visit the website of the ISP or router manufacturer or contact them directly.
6. To restart the Roku device, either unplug the power cable, wait a moment, and then reconnect it or use the following steps from the Settings menu: Select System, select Power, and select System restart.
7. Review the results of the most recent connection check by visiting Settings > Network > About.

- Error code 012 and Error code 013: Ethernet cable related issues. Unplug your Ethernet cable then plug it back in, or try a different one.
- Error code 018: Slow internet speed issues. You may want to consider upgrading your internet to a faster connection.
- Error code 009, Error code 14, Error code 14.10, Error code 14.11, Error code 14.30, Error code 14.50, Error code 14.62, and Error code 14.64: Connectivity issues. Restart your router and Roku device.

Solutions:
- Re-enter password.
- Move Roku device closer to wireless router.
- Unplug and plug Ethernet cable or try a different one.
- Upgrade internet to a faster connection.
- Restart router and Roku device.

Error code descriptions: Not provided in the text.

Solutions:
- Wait a few minutes and try the software update again.
- Check for an alert on the Roku support site indicating an extended outage.
- Check that the Roku device is connected to the correct network.
- Check that the router is working properly.
- Check for a strong enough wireless signal.
- Restart the Roku device and router.

Title:What to do if you see error code 011 (Cannot connect to Roku) | Official Roku Support
Error code 011 - Cannot connect to Roku:

Description: Error code 011 indicates the software update has failed because your Roku device is unable to connect to the Roku Software Update Server.

Solution:
1. Wait a few minutes and select Try again
2. Go to support.roku.com and check to see if there are any alerts indicating that the service is currently experiencing problems.
3. If the Roku device detects that it is no longer connected to the Internet, you will see a message leading you through the process of re-connecting to your home network. 

Note: No other error codes were mentioned in the text.
